  "prompt": "Is it too late for any age person to learn computer programing?",
  "response": "No, it's never too late for anyone to learn computer programming. People of all ages can learn to code, and many do so successfully. Your ability to learn programming depends more on your dedication, interest, and the time you can commit to practice than on your age. There are numerous resources available for learners of all levels, including online courses, tutorials, books, and coding boot camps. Whether you're a young student or a senior, starting with the basics and gradually progressing to more advanced topics can make the learning journey manageable and enjoyable. Additionally, programming can be a rewarding skill that opens up various opportunities, both personally and professionally.",
